Adjust rack to middle position (top and middle positions for 8 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a #large pot{} (two large pots for 8) of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced).

Generously coat a #9-by-13-inch baking dish{} (two 9-by-13-inch baking dishes for 8) with @nonstick cooking spray{} and set aside.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{12%ounce} to #pot{} (for 8 servings, divide between two large pots or cook in batches). Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water (1 cup for 8), then drain.

Meanwhile, open package of @chicken breast strips{20%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add chicken, scallion whites, onion, and bell pepper in a single layer; season with @fajita spice blend{2%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through and onion is tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches, adding another drizzle of oil for each batch. Be sure not to overcrowd the pan for even browning!

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @cream sauce base{8%ounce}, @diced tomatoes{14%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, half the @tex-mex paste{1}, and two packets of @mexican cheese blend{1.5%cup} (all the Tex-Mex paste and four packets of Mexican cheese blend for 8 servings).

Transfer drained penne and chicken mixture to bowl with sauce; stir to thoroughly combine.

> If sauce seems too thick, add splashes of reserved pasta cooking water until everything is thoroughly coated.

Transfer pasta mixture to prepared baking dish (divide between two prepared baking dishes for 8 servings).

Cover baking dish tightly with #foil{}; set on top of a foil-lined #baking sheet{} (two baking sheets for 8).

> The baking sheet will help protect your oven from any sauce that may bubble over!

Bake on middle rack until bubbly, ~{30%minutes} (bake on top and middle racks for 8 servings).

> Lift the foil carefully to check on the pasta bake—there might be some steam!

Remove baking sheet with baking dish from oven. Carefully remove and discard foil from baking dish; stir pasta bake. Sprinkle with remaining Mexican cheese blend; return baking sheet with baking dish to oven and bake, uncovered, until cheese melts, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

Let pasta bake rest at least ~{5%minutes} before serving.

Garnish with scallion greens and serve family style directly from baking dish.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.